The Chronicle By Tawanda Mudimu HISTORY was made in Bulawayo today as the city, for the first time since 1980, hosted the country’s main Independence celebrations at Barbourfields Stadium in line with the Second Republic’s devolution and decentralisation thrust. <img class="size-full wp-image-601171" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-75.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-75.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-75-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa inspects the parade The Independence Day celebrations are being held under the theme: “Zim@ 42 — Leaving no one and no place behind.” <img class="size-full wp-image-601182" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-71.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-71.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-71-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa marches past the parade  In the past, Independence Day celebrations were held in Harare. <img class="size-full wp-image-601177" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-73.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-73.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-73-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> For the first time Bulawayo hosted the main Independence celebrations Thousands of Zimbabweans are gathered at the iconic football field for the momentous event that has been spiced up by entertainment from schoolchildren, musicians, Zimbabwe Defence Forces, Zimbabwe Republic Police, Zimbabwe Prisons and Correctional Service drills, among others. <img class="size-full wp-image-601164" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-70.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-70.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-70-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The First Family at the State House in the morning President Mnangagwa presided over the celebrations and delivered the keynote address. <img class="size-full wp-image-601168" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-67.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-67.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Independence-67-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa delivers the keynote address 